{
  "id": "L21",
  "title": "At the Pharmacy",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome! In this lesson, you'll learn how to pick up a prescription at a German pharmacy, 'die Apotheke'. Remember to use the formal 'Sie' when speaking to the pharmacist."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V01",
      "data": {
        "Die Apotheke": "The pharmacy"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L21_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Apotheke",
        "phonetic": "/apoˈteːkə/",
        "tip": "The 'th' in German is pronounced like a hard 't', not like in the English word 'the'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Guten Tag",
        "meaning": "Good day"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V02",
      "data": {
        "Das Rezept": "The prescription"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich möchte ein Rezept abholen",
        "meaning": "I would like to pick up a prescription"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In the phrase 'Ich möchte ein Rezept abholen', the second verb 'abholen' (to pick up) is pushed to the end of the sentence. This is a common pattern in German."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Wie ist Ihr Name?",
        "meaning": "What is your name? (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Mein Name ist...",
        "meaning": "My name is..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hier, bitte",
        "meaning": "Here you are"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Vielen Dank",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Einen Moment, bitte",
        "meaning": "One moment, please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L21_S01",
      "title": "Stating Your Needs",
      "setting": "You enter a pharmacy to pick up a prescription.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet the pharmacist",
          "chatbot_message": "Guten Tag!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say you want to pick up a prescription",
          "chatbot_message": "Gerne. Wie ist Ihr Name?"
        },
        {
          "title": "State your name",
          "chatbot_message": "Danke, {user_name}. Haben Sie das Rezept hier?",
          "extract_info": {
            "user_name": "Extract the user's name from their message"
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Hand over the prescription",
          "chatbot_message": "Vielen Dank. Einen Moment, bitte."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hier ist...",
        "meaning": "Here is..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V03",
      "data": {
        "Ihr": "Your (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V04",
      "data": {
        "Das Medikament": "The medicine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Wie oft?",
        "meaning": "How often?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Soll ich...?",
        "meaning": "Should I...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V05",
      "data": {
        "Nehmen": "To take"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To ask a question like 'Should I take...?', you start with the verb 'Soll ich...?' and put the other verb, 'nehmen', at the very end."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Sie sollen...",
        "meaning": "You should... (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V06",
      "data": {
        "Dreimal pro Tag": "Three times per day"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Vor dem Essen",
        "meaning": "Before the meal"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E13",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Nach dem Essen",
        "meaning": "After the meal"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V07",
      "data": {
        "Oder": "Or"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E14",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Brauche ich...?",
        "meaning": "Do I need...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V08",
      "data": {
        "Die Schmerzmittel": "The painkillers"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V09",
      "data": {
        "Nein": "No"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V10",
      "data": {
        "Keine": "No / not any"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Use 'keine' to negate a noun. For example, 'Ich brauche keine Schmerzmittel' means 'I do not need any painkillers'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E15",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Sonst noch etwas?",
        "meaning": "Anything else?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L21_S02",
      "title": "Asking for Instructions",
      "setting": "The pharmacist returns with your medicine and you have some questions.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask how often to take the medicine",
          "chatbot_message": "Hier ist Ihr Medikament."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if it's before or after meals",
          "chatbot_message": "Sie sollen das Medikament dreimal pro Tag nehmen."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if you also need painkillers",
          "chatbot_message": "Nach dem Essen, bitte."
        },
        {
          "title": "React to the final question",
          "chatbot_message": "Nein, Sie brauchen keine Schmerzmittel. Sonst noch etwas?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E16",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Nein, danke. Das ist alles.",
        "meaning": "No, thanks. That is all."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V11",
      "data": {
        "Die Versicherung": "The insurance"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V12",
      "data": {
        "Bezahlen": "To pay"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E17",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Bezahlt die Versicherung das?",
        "meaning": "Does the insurance pay for that?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To ask a yes/no question like this, simply put the conjugated verb ('bezahlt') at the beginning of the sentence."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V13",
      "data": {
        "Fast alles": "Almost everything"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V14",
      "data": {
        "Nur": "Only"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L21_V15",
      "data": {
        "Der Euro": "The Euro"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E18",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich bezahle mit Karte",
        "meaning": "I'll pay by card"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E19",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "In Ordnung",
        "meaning": "Alright / Okay"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E20",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Auf Wiedersehen",
        "meaning": "Goodbye (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E21",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Schönen Tag noch",
        "meaning": "Have a nice day"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L21_E22",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ihnen auch",
        "meaning": "You too (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L21_S03",
      "title": "Payment and Closing",
      "setting": "You're ready to pay for your medicine and finish the conversation.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Say that's all and ask about insurance",
          "chatbot_message": "Sonst noch etwas?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say how you will pay",
          "chatbot_message": "Die Versicherung bezahlt fast alles. Sie bezahlen nur 5 Euro."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the pharmacist and say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "In Ordnung."
        },
        {
          "title": "Finish the conversation",
          "chatbot_message": "Vielen Dank. Ihnen auch einen schönen Tag. Auf Wiedersehen!"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}